snippet.textDisplay: You may already be doing this but baby should be doing "tummy time" at this age rather than sitting. Tummy time helps his muscles strengthen in order to then learn to roll over, sit, crawl, push up. Also, su dedo no se le va a secar. Yo se que las abuelitas eso le decian a uno. But him sucking his hand/finger is actually very good sensory stimulation. Up until about age 2, babies learn to know the world through oral motor sensory stimuli. In other words' they learn about the world through their mouth. That's why they always put stuff in their mouth, because they're learning/exploring and it's stimulating 😊
